1. What is a Denial of Service (DoS) Attack?

A DoS attack is when an attacker intentionally sends too many requests or malformed traffic to a target system (website, server, API) to make it:

Slow

Unresponsive

Completely unavailable

ğŸ‘‰ The goal is service disruption, not data theft.

