What is a Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) Attack?

A DDoS attack is a DoS attack launched from multiple systems at the same time, often from a botnet.

A botnet = thousands or millions of infected computers (â€œbotsâ€) controlled by a hacker (command & control server).

Example:

1 hacker controls 20,000 infected devices

Sends traffic simultaneously to the victim

Server crashes instantly

ğŸ‘‰ DDoS = higher power, harder to stop.
